article.headline: Campbell 54, North Florida 49
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez's double-double helped Campbell defeat North Florida 54-49 on Thursday night. Rodriguez finished with 14 points and 15 rebounds -- both game highs -- while Eric Smith added 14 points for the Camels (9-10, 4-5 Atlantic Sun), who led 22-20 at the break. Reggie Bishop chipped in 10 points. Campbell went 57.9 percent from the free-throw line to North Florida's 50 percent. North Florida hit 40.4 percent of its field goal attempts, while Campbell hit 31 percent. James Grimball led North Florida (2-18,0-10 A-Sun) with 15 points, while Arnold Henry and Chris Timberlake each added eight points.
